01/11/21, 10:39 - +91 90272 17998: *Syllabus for MID SEM*

*Discrete Maths* :-

Unit I and Unit III
Unit I - Sets, Relations, Functions and POSET, Lattice etc.
Unit III - Fundamental of Logic And Methods of Proof

*Data Structures* :-

Unit I and II
Unit I - Introduction, Pointers, memory Allocation, Complexity, Arrays, Stack, Stack Operations, Recusrion
Unit II - Queues and Linked List

*OOPs with C++*

Unit I and II
Unit I - Introduction: Need of object oriented programming, Overview of C++,Header Files and Namespaces,  Basic of C++ programming, arrays and strings, pointers & user-defined types Function Components, argument passing ,inline functions, recursive functions.

Unit II - Classes & Objects, Operator overloading

*Logic Design* :-

Unit I and II
Unit I - Review of Number System, Boolean Algebra and Gate Level Minimization
Unit II - Combinational Logic Circuit (only up to multiplexers)

*Fundamental of Cyber Security* :-

Unit I and II
Unit I - Introduction to Cyber Security
Unit II - Linux Basics and Scripting for Ethical Hacking, Introduction to Bash Scripting, Introduction to Python

*Cloud Computing* :-

Uni I and II
Unit I - Introduction to Cloud Computing ,Advantages, History, Infrastructure, Security, Applications, Cloud Service provider etc.

Unit II - Introduction to Big data, Advantages, History and characteristics, Types of Data, Data Quality, Data Mining and techniques, Tools used for mining, etc 


For detailed topics and syllabus refer the SYLLABUS PDF on moodle.

09/11/21, 02:16 - +91 90272 17998: *Syllabus for MID SEM*

*Discrete Maths* :-

Unit I and Unit III
Unit I - Sets, Relations, Functions and POSET, Lattice etc.
Unit III - Fundamental of Logic And Methods of Proof

*Data Structures* :-

Unit I and II
Unit I - Introduction, Pointers, memory Allocation, Complexity, Arrays, Stack, Stack Operations, Recusrion
Unit II - Queues and Linked List

*OOPs with C++*

Unit I and II
Unit I - Introduction: Need of object oriented programming, Overview of C++,Header Files and Namespaces,  Basic of C++ programming, arrays and strings, pointers & user-defined types Function Components, argument passing ,inline functions, recursive functions.

Unit II - Classes & Objects, Operator overloading

*Logic Design* :-

Unit I and II
Unit I - Review of Number System, Boolean Algebra and Gate Level Minimization
Unit II - Combinational Logic Circuit (only up to multiplexers)

*Fundamental of Cyber Security* :-

Unit I and II
Unit I - Introduction to Cyber Security
Unit II - Linux Basics and Scripting for Ethical Hacking, Introduction to Bash Scripting, Introduction to Python

*Cloud Computing* :-

Uni I and II
Unit I - Introduction to Cloud Computing ,Advantages, History, Infrastructure, Security, Applications, Cloud Service provider etc.

Unit II - Introduction to Big data, Advantages, History and characteristics, Types of Data, Data Quality, Data Mining and techniques, Tools used for mining, etc 


For detailed topics and syllabus refer the SYLLABUS PDF on moodle.

09/12/21, 11:05 - +91 89233 45771: The NEO Educational Foundation presents to you 
*The 5th National Engineering Olympiad*!

The National Engineering Olympiad is a competitive platform for the engineering students to showcase your aptitude skills and represent yourself at the national level.

Register now!
https://nationalolympiad.org/?refid=315960612

*The Rounds:*
Similar to the previous four editions of the National Engineering Olympiad, the exam will be conducted in two rounds.

Round 1: Basic Aptitude Test- 60 mins, 60 questions. 
Dates are 8th & 9th December 2021. 
Round 2: Technical Ability Test- Online MCQ Exam based on your syllabus of the year & branch you are studying in. 

*Please Note:*
Both rounds are to be attempted _online_ from your home!

*The Rewards:* 

_For the top performers:_
-Top 10 of each year & branch will be awarded a Medal of Excellence.
-Top 30 of each year & branch will be awarded a Certificate of Excellence.

_For all participants:_
-Guaranteed Internships in various domains.
-A national-level participation certificate.
-Career-oriented webinars by experts for free.

(More details are available on the website)

Hurry up! Last day to register for Phase 2 is 7th December.
Visit https://nationalolympiad.org/?refid=315960612

13/12/21, 10:47 - +91 89233 45771: The NEO Educational Foundation presents to you 
*The 5th National Engineering Olympiad*!

The National Engineering Olympiad is a competitive platform for the engineering students to showcase your aptitude skills and represent yourself at the national level.

Register now!
https://nationalolympiad.org/?refid=315960612

*The Rounds:*
Similar to the previous four editions of the National Engineering Olympiad, the exam will be conducted in two rounds.

Round 1: Basic Aptitude Test- 60 mins, 60 questions. 
Dates are 18th & 19th December 2021. 
Round 2: Technical Ability Test- Online MCQ Exam based on your syllabus of the year & branch you are studying in. 

*Please Note:*
Both rounds are to be attempted _online_ from your home!

*The Rewards:* 

_For the top performers:_
-Top 10 of each year & branch will be awarded a Medal of Excellence.
-Top 30 of each year & branch will be awarded a Certificate of Excellence.

_For all participants:_
-Guaranteed Internships in various domains.
-A national-level participation certificate.
-Career-oriented webinars by experts for free.

(More details are available on the website)

Hurry up! The last day to register for Phase 3 is 17th December.
Visit https://nationalolympiad.org/?refid=315960612

14/12/21, 09:41 - +91 98351 67276: #include<iostream>

using namespace std;

class matrix{
public:
    int mat[3][3];
    void getdata(){
    cout<<"Enter data for the 3*3 matrix:";
    for(int i=0;i<3;++i)
    {
        for(int j=0;j<3;++j){
            cout<<"Enter the data for ["<<(i+1)<<"]["<<(j+1)<<"] :";
            cin>>mat[i][j];
        }
    }
}
   matrix operator++(){
       for(int i=0;i<3;++i)
       {
           for(int j=0;j<3;++j)
            mat[i][j]++;
       }
   }
   void display(){
   for(int i=0;i<3;++i){
    for(int j=0;j<3;++j)
    {
        cout<<" "<<mat[i][j]<<" ";
    }
    cout<<endl;
   }
}
};

int main(){
   matrix ob1;
   ob1.getdata();
   cout<<"Before increment:\n";
   ob1.display();
   ++ob1;
   cout<<"After increment:\n";
   ob1.display();
   return 0;
}

20/12/21, 09:02 - +91 81262 69186: #include<stdio.h>
#include<stdlib.h>

struct node
{
    int info ;
    struct node *left;
    struct node *right;
};

void Create_Tree(struct node **root , int val )
{
    
    struct node *new_node;
    new_node=NULL;
    if(*root == NULL)
    {
    new_node = (struct node*)malloc(sizeof(struct node));
    new_node->left=NULL;
    new_node->right=NULL;
    new_node->info=val;
    *root=new_node;
    return;
    }

    if(val < (*root)->info)
    {
        Create_Tree(&(*root)->left , val);
    }

    else if(val > (*root)->info)
    {
        Create_Tree(&(*root)->right , val);
    }

}

int count_Node(struct node *root)
{
   static int count = 0;
    
    
     if(root != NULL)
    {
        
        printf(" %d  ",root->info);
        ++count;
        count_Node(root->left);
        count_Node(root->right);
        
      
    }
    
    return count;
    
}

/* Function to get the count of leaf nodes in a binary tree*/
 int getLeafCount(struct node* node)
{
  if(node == NULL)      
    return 0;
  if(node->left == NULL && node->right==NULL)     
    return 1;           
  else
    return getLeafCount(node->left) + getLeafCount(node->right);  
              
}

int main()
{
    int val ;
    struct node *root;
    root = NULL;

    int x=1;
    while(x==1)
    {
        printf("Enter a number for Create tree : ");
        scanf("%d",&val);

        Create_Tree(&root,val);

        printf("If You wnat to create tree press 1 otherwise press any number : ");
        scanf("%d",&x);
    }

    int c;
    c=count_Node(root);
    printf("\nTotal node : %d\n",c );
    /*get leaf count of the above created tree*/
  printf("Leaf count of the tree is %d", getLeafCount(root));
   

    return 0;

}

14/01/22, 14:27 - +91 70185 37775: Advantages:
Operator overloading in c++ enables programmers to use notation closer to the target domain.
They provide similar support to built-in types of user-defined types.
Operator overloading in c++ makes the program easier to understand.
The need for operator overloading:
It allows us to provide an intuitive interface to our class users, plus makes it possible for templates to work equally well with classes and built-in types. Operator overloading allows C++ operators to have user-defined meanings on user-defined types or classes.
14/01/22, 14:27 - +91 70185 37775: #include <iostream>
using namespace std;

class Complex {
    int real, imag;

   public:
    Complex(int x = 0, int y = 0) {
        real = x;
        imag = y;
    }
    void display() {
        cout << real << " + i(" << imag << ")" << endl;
    }

    friend Complex operator+(int z, Complex B);
};

Complex operator+(int z, Complex B) {
    Complex A;
    A.real = z + B.real;
    A.imag = B.imag;
    return A;
}

int main() {
    Complex obj1(1, 1), obj2(0, 0);
    obj2 = 10 + obj1;
    obj2.display();
}

01/02/22, 11:17 - +91 77177 04643: Race around condn.
Why toggling happens?
Why BCD to excess 3 conversion?
Half adder using min no of nand gates.
Combinational circuit which has 3 input and output when majority no of input are high otherwise low.
64:1 k mux using 2:1
Mux se decoder kse banega

Mod 10 counter kya hota h

Selection line kse decide hpti h mux m

64:1 mux kitne 4:1 se banega

Sr se jk banane m s ki input state kya hoti h

21/03/22, 22:42 - Anushka Agarwal Btech F (CR): Debug Your Soul

‚ÄúDebugging is being the detective in a crime movie, where the murderer is also you.‚Äù
Hola Everyone,üëã
Keeping in mind our community‚Äôs vision statement to make you all technically sound and up to date in the IT industry, the GEU ACM Student Chapter is proud to organize a really exciting competition event named, ‚ÄúDebug Your Soul‚Äùüíª. As upcoming leaders in technology, we‚Äôre always looking for ways to improve ourselves. That‚Äôs the nature of our profession. That said, it‚Äôs not uncommon for us to hate debugging. We‚Äôll get a bug report and cry in exasperation, ‚ÄúI want to build stuff! Not fix bugs!‚Äùüòì. But that‚Äôs not the right attitude to have towards bugs and debugging in general.
That‚Äôs because debugging doesn‚Äôt only happen when you‚Äôre fixing bugs in bug reports. We spend a lot of time debugging when writing brand new code too. How often have you written code that didn‚Äôt work on the first try and that you had to debug? (We‚Äôve all had that happen more often than we want to admit!)üôã
That‚Äôs why debugging is such an important skill to have. We spend a ridiculous amount of time debugging. Yet we never think about how getting better at it might also help us write better code.‚òëÔ∏è

üì¢ Who should attend?
üëâ Any student who gets a kick out of Debugging
üëâ Who wants to increase his/her skills
üëâ Who wants to master the art of TIME-MANAGEMENT
üëâ Who wants to connect with people of the same interests

üì¢ What will you gain?
üëâ Optimization techniques, so that you write efficient and beautiful codes with ease.üíπ

05/04/22, 14:58 - Harsh Rastogi B-24 Btech F: GEU IEEE is happy to announce a GEURE 2022 for all the students of Graphic Era (Deemed to Be University) and Graphic Era Hill University. The theme of the GEURE 2022 is based on UN17 Sustainable goals of development formulated by United Nations, each team has to pick up a goal and make a power point presentation in SIH format, on how to apply it, before the event. The presentation has to printed on A4 sized sheets (each slide on one page) and should be brought along on the day of the event where each team will be provided with chart papers and a glue stick. Each team has to paste their A4 sized printouts on the chart paper and explain their solution to the judges.
E-certificates will be given to all participants, volunteers and organizers.Team is with minimum of 1 and maximum of 3 participants are allowed.

There are three prizes that will be given to the deserving teams: Best Innovation Award, People's Choice Award, and Best Research Award.
Event Date: 8th April, 2022. 
Timings: 02:00 PM to 04:00 PM.
Venue: CSIT  Block
Payment Detail: Rs. 100 per person
Google Form: https://forms.gle/ppFTYSgWcrSJeT9eA
IEEE membership form: https://forms.gle/kBSTxJSKUBLAtU6r5

//Anushka Agarwal

import java.util.*;
public class BankDeposit 
{

	public static void main(String[] args) 
	{
		Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
		while(true){
		System.out.println("Enter 1 for term deposit and 2 for recurring deposit and 3 to exit");
		
		int choice=sc.nextInt();
		
		switch(choice)
		{
		case 1:
		{
			System.out.println("Enter the principal amount, rate of interest and time period in years");
			double p=sc.nextDouble();
			double r=sc.nextDouble();
			double n=sc.nextDouble();
			
			double a=0;
			a=p*(1+(0.01*r))*n;
			System.out.println(a);
			break;
		}
		case 2:
		{
			System.out.println("Enter monthly installment, rate of interest, and time period in months");
			double p=sc.nextDouble();
			double r=sc.nextDouble();
			double n=sc.nextDouble();
			
			double a=0;
			
			a= p*r + p*n*(n+1)/2*r/100*1/12;
			System.out.println(a);
			break;
		}
		
		case 3:
			System.out.println("...........EXIT...........");
			System.exit(0);
			break;
			
		default:
			System.out.println("Invalid choice");
		}
		
		}
	}

}

//Anushka Agarwal
import java.util.*;
public class FriendlyPair 
{
	public static void main(String args[])
	{
	Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
	System.out.println("Enter the numbers to be checked");
	int num1=sc.nextInt();
	int num2=sc.nextInt();
	
	int sum1=0,sum2=0 ;
	for(int i=1;i<=num1/2;i++)
	{
		if(num1%i==0)
			sum1+=i;
	}
	for(int i=1;i<=num2/2;i++)
	{
		if(num2%i==0)
			sum2+=i;
	}
	if(sum1==num1 && sum2==num2)
		System.out.println("Friendly Pair");
	else
		System.out.println("Not Friendly Pair");
	}
}

import java.util.*;
public class Rep0to1 {

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		// TODO Auto-generated method stub
		
		Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
		
		System.out.println("Enter an integer");
		
		int num=sc.nextInt();
		int t=num;
		int n=0, rem=0,r=0;
		while(t!=0)
		{
			rem=t%10;
			if(rem==0)
				n=n*10+1;
			else
				n=n*10+rem;
			t=t/10;
		}
		t=0;
		while(n!=0)
		{
			r=n%10;
			t=t*10+r;
			n=n/10;
			
		}
		System.out.println(t);

	}

}

import java.util.*;
public class ZigZag {

	public static void main(String[] args) 
	{
		Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
		System.out.println("Enter the array size");
		int n=sc.nextInt();
		int arr[]=new int[n];
		
		for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
		{
			System.out.println("Enter the "+(i+1)+" th element");
			arr[i]=sc.nextInt();
		}
		boolean flag = true;
        
        int temp =0;
     
        for (int i=0; i<=arr.length-2; i++)
        {
            if (flag) 
            {
                
                if (arr[i] > arr[i+1])
                {
                  
                    temp = arr[i];
                    arr[i] = arr[i+1];
                    arr[i+1] = temp;
                }
                 
            }
            else 
            {
                if (arr[i] < arr[i+1])
                {
                    temp = arr[i];
                    arr[i] = arr[i+1];
                    arr[i+1] = temp;
                }
            }
            flag = !flag; 
        }
    for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
    {
    	System.out.print(arr[i]);
    }
	}	
}

import java.util.*;
public class SaddlePoint 
{
	public static void main(String[] args) 
	{
		Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
		System.out.println("Enter the number of rows and columns");
		int n=sc.nextInt();
		int m=sc.nextInt();
		int a[][]=new int[m][n];
		
		for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
		{
			
			for(int j=0;j<m;j++)
			{
				a[i][j]=sc.nextInt();
			}
		}
		int x=0;
		for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
		{
			int min=a[i][0];
			for(int j=0;j<m;j++)
			{
				int max=a[0][j];
				if( a[i][j]<min) 
					 min=a[i][j] ;
				if(a[i][j]>max)
				{
					max=a[i][j];
				}
				if(min==max)
					x=min;
			}
		}
		System.out.print(x);
	}

}

import java.util.*;
public class Pattern010 
{

	public static void main(String[] args) 
	{
		Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
		String str=sc.nextLine();
		 char last = str.charAt(0);
	     
	        int i = 1, counter = 0;
	        while (i < str.length())
	        {
	            if (str.charAt(i) == '1' && last == '0')
	            {
	                while (str.charAt(i) == '1')
	                    i++;
	     
	                if (str.charAt(i) == '0')
	                    counter++;
	            }
	     
	            last = str.charAt(i);
	            i++;
	        }
	        System.out.println(counter);
	}

}

import java.util.*;

public class VowDel 
{
	public static void main(String args[]) {
	Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
	System.out.println("Enter the String");
	String str=sc.nextLine();

	StringBuffer Str=new StringBuffer(str);
	int x=str.length();
	for(int i=0;i<x;i++) {
	char vowel= Str.charAt(i);
	  if((vowel=='A')||(vowel=='E')||(vowel=='I')||(vowel=='O')||(vowel=='U')||(vowel=='a')||(vowel=='e')||(vowel=='i')||(vowel=='o')||(vowel=='u'))
	  {
		  Str.deleteCharAt(i);
		  x--;
	  }
	  
	
	}
	System.out.println(Str.toString());
}
}

import java.util.*;
public class Rearrange {

	public static void main(String[] args) {
	 Scanner sc= new Scanner(System.in);
	 System.out.println("Enter the array size");
		int n=sc.nextInt();
		int a[]=new int[n];
		
		for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
		{
			System.out.println("Enter the "+(i+1)+" th element");
			a[i]=sc.nextInt();
		}
		
		for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
		{
			for(int j=i+1;j<n;j++)
			{
				if(a[j]<0)
				{
					if(a[i]>0)
					{
						int temp=a[j];
						a[j]=a[i];
						a[i]=temp;
					}
				}
			}
		}
		
	    
		for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
		{
			System.out.println(a[i]);
		}
	

	}

}

	class Bank{
		String name,add;
		int acc_no;
		double bal;
		
		Bank(int x){
			name=add="";
			acc_no=x;
			bal=0;
		}
		
		void get_info(){
			Scanner sc= new Scanner(System.in);
			System.out.print("Enter name:");
			name = sc.nextLine();
			System.out.print("Enter Address:");
			add = sc.nextLine();
			System.out.print("Enter balance:");
			bal=sc.nextInt();
			sc.nextLine();
		}
		
		void display_info(){
			System.out.println("Name:"+name);
			System.out.println("Address:"+add);
			System.out.println("Account No.:"+acc_no);
			System.out.println("Balance:"+bal+"\n");
		}
		
		void add_bal(double amt){
			bal+=amt;
			System.out.println("Balance:"+bal+"\n");
		}
		
		void withdraw(double amt){
			if(amt>bal)
				System.out.println("Insufficient funds"+"\n");
			else 
				bal=bal-amt;
			System.out.println("Balance:"+bal+"\n");
		}
		
		void ch_add(String adder){
			add=adder;
			System.out.println("The new address is:"+add+"\n");
		}
		
		public static void main(String args[]){
			Scanner sc = new Scanner (System.in);
			int n,flag=1;
			int x=1001;
			double amt;
			System.out.print("Enter the number of depositors:");
			n=sc.nextInt();
			Bank[] arr= new Bank[n];
			for(int i =0;i<n;++i){
				System.out.println("Enter details for "+(i+1)+" account:"+"\n");
				arr[i]=new Bank(x);
				arr[i].get_info();
				x++;
				System.out.println();
			}
			int ch;
			do{
				System.out.println("1.Print Details\n2.Add amount to account\n3.Withdraw amount from account\n4.Change Address\n5. Exit");
				System.out.print("Enter choice:");
				ch=sc.nextInt();
				if(ch<5){
					System.out.print("Enter the account number:");
					int acc=sc.nextInt();
					for(int i =0;i<n;++i){
						if(arr[i].acc_no==acc){
							switch(ch){
								case 1: arr[i].display_info();
										break;
								case 2: System.out.print("Enter the amount to be added to balance:");
										amt=sc.nextDouble();
										arr[i].add_bal(amt);
										break;
								case 3: System.out.print("Enter the amount to be withdrawn:");
										amt=sc.nextDouble();
										arr[i].withdraw(amt);
										break;
								case 4: sc.nextLine();
										System.out.print("Enter new address:");
										String addr=sc.nextLine();
										arr[i].ch_add(addr);
										break;
							}
							flag=1;
						}
					}
					if(flag==0)
						System.out.println("Account not found!");
				}
				else if(ch>5)
					System.out.print("Wrong Choice");
			}while(ch!=5);
		}
	} //Q 10
18/04/22, 20:08 - +91 79830 46533: import java.util.*;
class WordExample{
	private String strdata;
	
	WordExample(String x){
		x=x.trim().toUpperCase();
		int len=x.length();
		char last=x.charAt(len-1);
		if(last!='!'&&last!='.'&&last!='?'){
			System.out.print("Invalid Input.");
			return;
		}
			strdata=x;
	}
	
	public static boolean isVowel(char ch){
		 ch = Character.toUpperCase(ch);
        boolean ret = false;
        if (ch == 'A'
            || ch == 'E'
            || ch == 'I'
            || ch == 'O'
            || ch == 'U')
            ret = true;
            
        return ret;
	}
		
	public static void main(String args[]){
		Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
		System.out.print("Enter a sentence:");
		String x = sc.nextLine();
		WordExample o1=new WordExample(x);
		StringTokenizer st= new StringTokenizer(x);
		StringBuffer vowel= new StringBuffer();
		StringBuffer cons= new StringBuffer();
		int c=0;
		while(st.hasMoreTokens()){
			String word=st.nextToken();
			int len=word.length();
			if(isVowel(word.charAt(0))&&isVowel(word.charAt(len-1))){
				vowel.append(word);
				vowel.append(" ");
				c++;
			}
			else{
				cons.append(word);
				cons.append(" ");
			}
		}
		String newStr =vowel.toString()+cons.toString();
		System.out.println("Number of words beginning and ending with vowels are:"+c);
		System.out.println	("New string is:"+newStr);
	}
}//Q11
18/04/22, 20:18 - +91 79830 46533: import java.util.*;

abstract class Shape{
	abstract void rectangleArea(float l,float b);
	abstract void squareArea(float a);
	abstract void circleArea(float r);
}

class Area extends Shape{
	void rectangleArea(float l, float b){
		System.out.println("The area of rectangle is:"+(l*b));
	}
	void squareArea(float a){
		System.out.println("The area of square is:"+(a*a));
	}
	void circleArea(float a){
		System.out.println("The area of circle is:"+(3.14*a*a));
	}
	
	public static void main(String argsp[]){
		Area o1=new Area();
		o1.rectangleArea(5,6);
		o1.squareArea(5);
		o1.circleArea(5);
	}
}//13

public class labFile_3 {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int num1,num2,sum1,sum2;
        System.out.print("Enter num1 and num2: ");
        num1=sc.nextInt();
        num2=sc.nextInt();
        sum1=num1;
        sum2=num2;
        sc.close();
        for(int i=1;i<=num1/2;i++){
            if(num1%i==0)
            sum1+=num1/i;
        }
        for(int i=1;i<=num2/2;i++){
            if(num2%i==0)
            sum2+=num2/i;
        }
        if(sum1/num1==sum2/num2)
        System.out.print("Friendly Pair");
        else
        System.out.print("Not Friendly Pair");
    }
}

        int num,n=0;
        System.out.print("Enter number: ");
        num=sc.nextInt();
        sc.close();
        while(num!=0){
            int dig=num%10;
            if(dig==0)
            dig=1;
            n=n*10+dig;
            num=num/10;
        }
        int temp=0;
        while(n!=0){
            int dig=n%10;
            temp=temp*10+dig;
            n/=10;
        }
        System.out.println("Changed number: "+temp);
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        int size,arr[],temp;
        size=sc.nextInt();
        arr= new int[size];
        for(int i=0;i<size;i++){
            arr[i]=sc.nextInt();
        }
        sc.close();
        for(int i=0;i<size-1;i++){
            if((arr[i]>arr[i+1])&&i%2==0){
                temp=arr[i];
                arr[i]=arr[i+1];
                arr[i+1]=temp;
            }
            else if(arr[i]<arr[i+1]&&(i%2!=0)){
                temp=arr[i];
                arr[i]=arr[i+1];
                arr[i+1]=temp;
            }
        }
        for(int i=0;i<size;i++)
        System.out.print(arr[i]+" ");
    }

19/04/22, 10:30 - +91 94118 55745: import java.util.*;
public class labFile_7 {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc= new Scanner(System.in);
        int n,m,matrix[][];
        System.out.print("Enter n and m: ");
        n=sc.nextInt();
        m=sc.nextInt();
        matrix=new int[n][m];
        System.out.println("Enter matrix elements: ");
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++) 
        for(int j=0;j<m;j++) matrix[i][j]=sc.nextInt();
        sc.close();
        int temp=0;
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            int min=Integer.MAX_VALUE,max=Integer.MIN_VALUE;
            for(int j=0;j<m;j++){
                if(min>matrix[i][j]){
                    min=matrix[i][j];
                    temp=j;
                }
            }
            for(int k=0;k<n;k++){
                if(max<matrix[k][temp]){
                    max=matrix[k][temp];
                }
            }
            if(max==min){
                temp=max;
                System.out.print("Saddle point is: "+temp);
            }
        }
    }
}

        System.out.println("Enter String: ");
        StringBuffer sb= new StringBuffer("");
        sb.append(sc.nextLine());
        sc.close();
        for(int i=0;i<sb.length();i++){
            if(sb.charAt(i)=='A'||sb.charAt(i)=='E'||sb.charAt(i)=='I'||sb.charAt(i)=='O'||sb.charAt(i)=='U'||sb.charAt(i)=='a'||sb.charAt(i)=='e'||sb.charAt(i)=='i'||sb.charAt(i)=='o'||sb.charAt(i)=='u'){
                sb.replace(i, i+1, "");
                i--;
            }
        }
        System.out.println(sb);
    }
}

19/04/22, 10:31 - +91 94118 55745: public class labFile_13 {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Area a= new Area(10,11,12,13);
        System.out.println("Area of Rectangle: "+a.rectangleArea());
        System.out.println("Area of Square: "+a.squareArea());
        System.out.println("Area of Circle: "+a.circleArea());
    }
}
abstract class Shape{
    int l,b,s,r;
    Shape(int l,int b,int s,int r){
        this.l=l;
        this.b=b;
        this.s=s;
        this.r=r;
    }
    protected abstract int rectangleArea();
    protected abstract int squareArea();
    protected abstract double circleArea();
}
class Area extends Shape{
    Area(int l,int b,int s,int r){
        super(l,b,s,r);
    }
    public int rectangleArea(){
        return l*b;
    }
    public int squareArea(){
        return s*s;
    }
    public double circleArea(){
        return 3.14*(double)r*(double)r;
    }
}

abstract class Temperature{
    protected double temp;
    public void setTempData(double temp){
        this.temp=temp;
    }
    protected abstract void changeTemp();
}
class Fahrenheit extends Temperature{
    Fahrenheit(){

    }
    private double ctemp;
    public void changeTemp() {
        ctemp=(5.0/9.0)*(temp-32);
        System.out.println("Temperature in Celsius: "+ctemp);
    }
}
class Celsius extends Temperature{
    Celsius(){

    }
    private double ftemp;
    public void changeTemp(){
        ftemp=(9.0/5.0)*temp+32;
        System.out.println("Temperature in Fahrenheit: "+ftemp);
    }
}

public class labFile_15 {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc= new Scanner(System.in);
        double r,h;
        System.out.println("Enter radius and height of cone: ");
        r=sc.nextDouble();
        h=sc.nextDouble();
        Cone c = new Cone(r, h);
        c.volume();
        System.out.println("Enter radius of hemisphere: ");
        r=sc.nextDouble();
        Hemisphere hem = new Hemisphere(r);
        hem.volume();
        System.out.println("Enter radius and height of cylinder: ");
        r=sc.nextDouble();
        h=sc.nextDouble();
        Cylinder cy = new Cylinder(r, h);
        cy.volume();
        sc.close();
    }
}
interface Cal_Volume{
    public abstract void volume();
}
class Cone implements Cal_Volume{
    private double r,h;
    Cone(double r, double h){
        this.r=r;
        this.h=h;
    }
    public void volume(){
        System.out.println("Volume of Cone: "+(1.0/3.0)*3.14*r*r*h);
    }
}
class Hemisphere implements Cal_Volume{
    private double r;
    Hemisphere(double r){
        this.r=r;
    }
    public void volume(){
        System.out.println("Volume of Hemisphere: "+(2.0/3.0)*3.14*r*r*r);
    }
}
class Cylinder implements Cal_Volume{
    private double r,h;
    Cylinder(double r, double h){
        this.r=r;
        this.h=h;
    }
    public void volume(){
        System.out.println("Volume of Cylinder: "+3.14*r*r*h);
    }
}

21/04/22, 12:14 - +91 77177 04643: class Solution {
public:
    int maxArea(vector<int>& height) {
     int maxArea=0;
     int n=height.size();
        int i=0,j=n-1;
        int cArea=0;
        while(i<j)
        {
            cArea=(j-i)*min(height[i],height[j]);
            if(maxArea<cArea)
            {
                maxArea=cArea;
            }
            height[i]<height[j]?i++:j--;
        }
        return maxArea;
    }
};

int min(int a, int b)
{
    int temp=a;
    if(temp>b)
        temp=b;
    return temp;

void maxArea(int* height, int heightSize){
    int water=0,i=0,j=heightSize-1,height1=0,width=0,MaxWater=0;
    for(i=0,j=heightSize-1; i<heightSize && i<j;)
    {
        height1=min(height[i],height[j]);
        width=j-i;
        water=height1*width;
        if(MaxWater<water)
            MaxWater=water;
        if(height[i]<height[j])
            i++;
        else
            j--;
    }
    printf("Max Water is :%d",MaxWater);
}

int trap(int* height, int heightSize){
    int *left=(int*)malloc(heightSize*sizeof(int));
    int *right=(int*)malloc(heightSize*sizeof(int));
    left[0]=height[0];
    right[heightSize-1]=height[heightSize-1];
    int i=0;
    for(i=1; i<heightSize; i++)
        left[i]=max(left[i-1],height[i]);
    for(i=heightSize-2; i>=0; i--)
        right[i]=max(right[i+1],height[i]);
    for(i=0; i<heightSize; i++)
        printf("%d ",left[i]);
    printf("\n");
     for(i=0; i<heightSize; i++)
        printf("%d ",right[i]);
     printf("\n");
    int trapwater=0;
    for(i=0; i<heightSize; i++)
        trapwater=trapwater+(min(left[i],right[i])-height[i]);
    return trapwater;
}

03/06/22, 16:13 - +91 98351 67276: #include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;
void printMaxActivities(int s[], int f[], int n)
{
	int i, j;

	cout <<"Following activities are selected "<< endl;
	i = 0;
	cout <<" "<< i;

	for (j = 1; j < n; j++)
	{
	if (s[j] >= f[i])
	{
		cout <<" " << j;
		i = j;
	}
	}
}
int main()
{ 
    int m,n;
    cin>>m;
    cin>>n;
    
	int s[m];
	for(int i=0;i<m;i++)
	{
	    cin>>s[i];
	}
	int f[n];
	for(int j=0;j<n;j++)
	{
	    cin>>f[j];
	}
	int o = sizeof(s)/sizeof(s[0]);
	printMaxActivities(s, f, o);
	return 0;
}

12/06/22, 11:11 - +91 74538 27506: #include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;
int gcd(int a,int b)
{
	if(a==0)
	{
		return b;
	}
	if(b==0)
	{
		return a;
	}
	if(a==b)
	{
		return a;
	}
	if(a>b)
	{
		return gcd(a-b,b);
	}
	return gcd(a,b-a);

}
int main() {
	int n;
	cin>>n;
	for(int i=1;i<=n;i++)
	{
		int a;int b;
		cin>>a>>b;
		int ans=gcd(a,b);
		cout<<ans<<endl;;
	}

}

using namespace std;

int main() {
	int n;
	vector<int>v;
	for(int i=1;i<=n;i++)
	{
		int a;
		cin>>a;
		v.push_back(a);
	}
		
	stack<int>st;	
	
	int N=v.size();int res=0;
	for(int i=0;i<N;++i)
	{
         while(!st.empty()&&v[i]<v[st.top()])
		 {
			int top=st.top();
			st.pop();
			 res=max(res,v[top]*(st.empty()?i:i-st.top()-1));
		 } 
		 st.push(i);

	}
	cout<<res;

	}

using namespace std;

int NonConstructibleChange (int coin[],int n) {
   sort(coin,coin+n);

   int currVal = 0;
   for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
   {
      if(coin[i]> currVal+1)
      return currVal+1;

      currVal+=coin[i];
   }
   return currVal+1;
}

int main() {
int n;
cin>> n;
int coin[n];
for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
{
   cin>>coin[i];
}

cout<<NonConstructibleChange(coin,n);
    
}

using namespace std;

int NonConstructibleChange (vector<int> nums) {
   int c=1;int n=nums.size();
   sort(nums.begin(),nums.end());
   for(int i=0;i<n&&nums[i]<=c;i++)
   {
      c=c+nums[i];
   }
   return c;

   


   
}

int main() {

    ios::sync_with_stdio(0);
    cin.tie(0);
    int n;
    cin >> n;
    vector<int> change(n);
    for(int i_change = 0; i_change < n; i_change++)
    {
    	cin >> change[i_change];
    }

    int out_;
    out_ = NonConstructibleChange(change);
    cout << out_;
}

13/07/22, 10:03 - +91 99923 41198: Dear participant,



Welcome to About AWS DeepRacer Student League ‚Äì India 2022



AWS DeepRacer gives you an interesting and fun way to get started with reinforcement learning (RL). RL is an advanced machine learning (ML) technique that takes a very different approach to training models than other machine learning methods. The AWS DeepRacer Student league returns in 2022 with new divisions and more opportunities to win than ever before! Students can now sign in to the league to learn machine learning, train models, and compete against other students from around the globe. 



Features of AWS DeepRacer Student League ‚Äì India 2022

i. All participants will get a global exposure in the preliminary race as they will compete in the AWS DeepRacer student.

ii. Top 100 racers will be evaluated by AWS Partners for employment opportunities in their respective organizations.

iii. All participants have an opportunity to win the AWS Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Machine Learning (ML) Scholarship program, in collaboration with Intel and Udacity.



Kindly find the attached meeting link for AWS DeepRacer Student League:

 

https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meetup-join/19%3agwUvbKzihjg211o9nuzGKoS_8rvhSyOdCZtVLh8dWOE1%40thread.tacv2/1657601981672?context=%7b%22Tid%22%3a%221490b17d-5dc9-4cbf-aeba-a2e854f521b8%22%2c%22Oid%22%3a%220977b50d-3078-4c68-b9cf-3dc1c3886568%22%7d

27/09/22, 12:33 - +91 98351 67276: //bisection method 
#include <math.h>
#include <stdio.h>

double f(double x) {
    return 6 * x * x + 11 * x - 35;
}

int main() {

    double c = 0, x0, x1;

    // calculating tolerance
    int noDigits = 4;
    double t = 0.5 * pow(10.0, -noDigits);

    x0 = 0;
    x1 = 0;

    // input range till valid range is found
    while (f(x0) * f(x1) > 0 || x0 == x1) {
        printf("Enter a valid range:: ");
        scanf("%lf %lf", &x0, &x1);
    }
    double x_prev = 0;

    printf("x0\t| c\t| x1\t| f(c)\n");
    while (1) {
        x_prev = c;
        c = (x0 + x1) / 2;
        printf("%lf\t| %lf\t| %lf\t| %lf\n", x0, c, x1, f(c));
        if (f(c) == 0) {
            printf("Result is :: %lf", c);
            break;
        } else if (f(x0) * f(c) < 0) {
            x1 = c;
        } else {
            x0 = c;
        }
        if (fabs(c - x_prev) <= t) {
            printf("Result is :: %lf  within %lf tolerance", c, t);
            break;
        }
    }
    return 0;
}

#include <stdio.h>
#include <math.h>

double f(double x) {
    return 6 * x * x + 11 * x - 35;
}

int main() {

    double c = 0, x0, x1;

    // calculating tolerance
    int noDigits = 4;
    double t = 0.5 * pow(10.0, -noDigits);

    x0 = 0;
    x1 = 0;

    // input range
    while (f(x0) * f(x1) > 0 || x0 == x1) {
        printf("Enter a valid range:: ");
        scanf("%lf %lf", &x0, &x1);
    }

    double x_prev = 0;
    printf("x0\t| c\t| x1\t| f(c)\n");
    while (1) {
        x_prev = c;
        c = (x0 * f(x1) - x1 * f(x0)) / (f(x1) - f(x0));
        printf("%lf\t| %lf\t| %lf\t| %lf\n", x0, c, x1, f(c));
        if (f(c) == 0) {
            printf("Result is :: %lf", c);
            break;
        } else if (f(x0) * f(c) < 0) {
            x1 = c;
        } else {
            x0 = c;
        }
        if (fabs(c - x_prev) < t) {
            printf("Result is :: %lf  within %lf tolerance", c, t);
            break;
        }
    }
    return 0;
}
27/09/22, 12:33 - +91 98351 67276: //newton raphson
#include<stdio.h>
#include<math.h>
#define e 0.000001
double f_(double x)
{
	return 3*x*x-4;
}
double f(double x)
{
    return x*x*x-4*x-9;
}
void newton_raphson(double x)
{
    double c=f(x)/f_(x);
	while(fabs(c)>=e)
    {
        c=f(x)/f_(x);
        x=x-c;
        printf("\n roots=%lf ",x);
    }
    printf("\nfinal root=%lf",x);
}
int main()
{
	double x;
	printf("enter x =");
	scanf("%lf",&x);
	newton_raphson(x);
    return 0;
}

07/11/22, 22:47 - +91 79830 46533: #include <stdio.h>
#include <math.h>
double f(double x)
{
    return x * x * x - x - 1;
}
double diff(double x)
{
    return 3 * x - 1;
}
int main()
{
    double a, b;
    printf("Please Enter Range :");
    scanf("%lf%lf", &a, &b);
    double f_a = f(a);
    double f_b = f(b);
    double x0, x1, temp;
    int i = 0;
    if (fabs(f_a) < fabs(f_b)) 
        x0 = a;
    else
        x0 = b;
    do
    {
        x1 = x0 - ((f(x0)) / diff(x0));
        x0 = x1;
        i++;
        temp = x0 - ((f(x0)) / diff(x0));
        printf("Iterations = %d || Root = %.5lf\n", i, x1);
    } while (fabs(temp - x1) > 0.00001);
    return 0;
}//newton raphson

int main(){
	int n;
	scanf("%d",&n);
	float A[n][n+1];
	float sol[n];
	for(int i=0;i<n;++i){
		for(int j=0;j<n+1;++j){
			scanf("%f",&A[i][j]);
		}
	}
	for(int i=0;i<n;++i){
		for(int j=0;j<n;++j){
			if(j>i){
				float c = A[j][i]/A[i][i];
				for(int k=0;k<n+1;++k)
					A[j][k] = A[j][k] - c*A[i][k];
			}
		}
	}
	sol[n-1]= A[n-1][n+1-1]/A[n-1][n-1];
	for(int i=n-2;i>=0;i--){
		float sum =0;
		for(int j =i+1;j<n;++j){
			sum+=A[i][j]*sol[j];
			printf("%f\n",sum);
		}
		sol[i] = (A[i][n-1+1]-sum)/A[i][i];
	}
	for(int i=0;i<n;++i)
		printf("\nx%d=%f\t",i,sol[i]);
	return 0;
}//gauss ele

int main(){
	int n;
	scanf("%d",&n);
	float A[n][n+1];
	float sol[n];
	for(int i=0;i<n;++i){
		for(int j=0;j<n+1;++j){
			scanf("%f",&A[i][j]);
		}
	}
	for(int i=0;i<n;++i){
		for(int j=0;j<n;++j){
            if(A[i][i]==0.0){
                printf("Mathematical Error");
                exit(0);
            }   
			if(i!=j){
				float c = A[j][i]/A[i][i];
				for(int k=0;k<n+1;++k)
					A[j][k] = A[j][k] - c*A[i][k];
			}
		}

07/11/22, 22:47 - +91 79830 46533: #include<stdio.h>
#include<math.h>
/*
Let the equations in diagonally ordered arrangement then modified be:
10x+y+z=15  -> x = (15-y-z)/10
x+10y+z=24  -> y = (24-x-z)/10
x+y+10z=33  -> z = (33-x-y)/10
*/

#define f1(x,y,z) (15-y-z)/10
#define f2(x,y,z) (24-x-z)/10
#define f3(x,y,z) (33-y-x)/10

int main(){
    float x0,y0,z0=0;//initial guess
    float x1,y1,z1;//next guesses
    float ex,ey,ez;//errors
    float e = 0.0001; // error limit
    do{
        x1 = f1(x0,y0,z0);
        y1 = f2(x1,y0,z0);
        z1 = f3(x1,y1,z0);

        //displaying 
        printf("%f\t%f\t%f\n",x1,y1,z1);

        ex = fabs(x1-x0);
        ey = fabs(y1-y0);
        ez = fabs(z1-z0);

        x0=x1;
        y0=y1;
        z0=z1;
    }while(ex>e && ey>e && ez> e);
    printf("Final Approximation:\nx=%f\ny=%f\nz=%f\n",x1,y1,z1);
    return 0;
}//gauss siedel
07/11/22, 22:47 - +91 79830 46533: #include <stdio.h>
#include <math.h>
#define f(x) (x*x*x)-x-1
int main()
{
    double a, b, c, pre;
    double fa, fb, fc;
    int i = 0;
    printf("A and B -> ");
    scanf("%lf %lf", &a, &b);
    do
    {
        fa = f(a);
        fb = f(b);
        c = (a + b) / 2.0;
        fc = f(c);
        pre = fc;
        if (fc < 0)
        {
            if (fa < 0)
                a = c;
            else
                b = c;
        }
        else if (fc > 0)
        {
            if (fb > 0)
                b = c;
            else
                a = c;
        }
        i++;
        printf("Iterations = %d || Root = %.3lf || Value = %lf\n", i, c, fc);
        c = (a + b) / 2.0;
        fc = f(c);
    } while ((fabs(fc - (pre)) > 0.00001));
    return 0;
}//bisection

12/12/22, 15:15 - Debjit Btech-F: #include<stdio.h>
#include<stdbool.h>
struct pid{
    int id,at,bt,st,ct;
};
int main()
{
    int n;
    float sum_tat=0,sum_wt=0;
    printf("Enter Number of Process: ");
    scanf("%d",&n);
    struct pid p[n];
    int wt[n],tat[n],st[n];
    for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
    {
            printf("Enter Arrival Time and Burst Time for Process %d: ",i+1);
            scanf("%d %d",&p[i].at,&p[i].bt);
            p[i].id=i+1;
    }
    bool iscompleted[n];
    for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
        iscompleted[i]=false;

    int completed=0,currenttime=0;

    while(completed!=n)
    {
        int min_idx=-1,mini=1000000;
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
        {
            if(p[i].at<=currenttime&&iscompleted[i]==false)
            {
                if(p[i].bt<mini)
                {
                    mini=p[i].bt;
                    min_idx=i;
                }
            }
        }
        if(min_idx==-1)
            currenttime++;
        else
        {
            p[min_idx].st=currenttime;
            p[min_idx].ct=p[min_idx].st+p[min_idx].bt;
            tat[min_idx]=p[min_idx].ct-p[min_idx].at;
            wt[min_idx]=tat[min_idx]-p[min_idx].bt;
             sum_tat +=tat[min_idx];
             sum_wt += wt[min_idx];
             completed++;
             iscompleted[min_idx]=true;
             currenttime=p[min_idx].ct;
        }

    }
    for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
    {
        printf("%d\n",p[i].ct);
    }
    printf("Average Waiting Time: %.2f\n Average Turn Around Time: %.2f",sum_wt/n,sum_tat/n);
}

int main()

  scanf("%d",&n); 
 printf("enter arrival time\n");
 for(i=0;i<n;i++)
 scanf("%d",&a[i]);
 printf("enter burst time\n");
 for(i=0;i<n;i++)
 scanf("%d",&b[i]); 
 for(i=0;i<n;i++)
 x[i]=b[i];

  b[9]=9999;
  
 for(time=0;count!=n;time++)
 {
   smallest=9;
  for(i=0;i<n;i++)
  {
   if(a[i]<=time && b[i]<b[smallest] && b[i]>0 )
   smallest=i;
  }
  b[smallest]--;
  if(b[smallest]==0)
  {
   count++;
   end=time+1;
   avg=avg+end-a[smallest]-x[smallest];
   tt= tt+end-a[smallest];
  }
 }
 printf("\n\nAverage waiting time = %lf\n",avg/n);
    printf("Average Turnaround time = %lf",tt/n);
    return 0;
}

16/12/22, 22:51 - Kulmeet Btech F: Send
16/12/22, 22:51 - Kulmeet Btech F: Codes
16/12/22, 22:51 - +91 79830 46533: #include<stdio.h>
#include<math.h>
/*
Let the equations in diagonally ordered arrangement then modified be:
10x+y+z=15  -> x = (15-y-z)/10
x+10y+z=24  -> y = (24-x-z)/10
x+y+10z=33  -> z = (33-x-y)/10
*/

#define f1(x,y,z) (15-y-z)/10
#define f2(x,y,z) (24-x-z)/10
#define f3(x,y,z) (33-y-x)/10

int main(){
    float x0,y0,z0=0;//initial guess
    float x1,y1,z1;//next guesses
    float ex,ey,ez;//errors
    float e = 0.0001; // error limit
    do{
        x1 = f1(x0,y0,z0);
        y1 = f2(x1,y0,z0);
        z1 = f3(x1,y1,z0);

        //displaying 
        printf("%f\t%f\t%f\n",x1,y1,z1);

        ex = fabs(x1-x0);
        ey = fabs(y1-y0);
        ez = fabs(z1-z0);

        x0=x1;
        y0=y1;
        z0=z1;
    }while(ex>e && ey>e && ez> e);
    printf("Final Approximation:\nx=%f\ny=%f\nz=%f\n",x1,y1,z1);
    return 0;
}

Position-1

Associate Software Engineer - DevTest/DevOPS (Internship + FTE)

The Associate Software Engineer - DevTest/DevOPS will report to the Director of Engineering, Mobile who will be helping our Engineering team to build quality in products that secure mobile devices, applications and data.

We develop innovative solutions that are transforming the internet security business, and millions of users rely on our services for data protection and comprehensive security. We also provide real-time analytics to our customers for unmatched visibility, and maintain a state-of-the-art NOC. The development team works on web filtering, policy enforcement, next-gen firewall, sandboxing, DLP, and mobile user solutions. Being responsive to our customers and delivering industry-leading mission-critical solutions require precise engineering and a philosophy of continuous improvement, both areas in which Zscaler engineers excel.

Responsibilities/What You‚Äôll Do

‚óè      Responsible for white box and unit testing complex features which includes implementing, automating and executing test cases.

‚óè      Identify and propose areas of improvement throughout the software development process.
‚óè      Work effectively in a fast-paced and constantly changing environment.
‚óè      Support production issues

Compensation Applicable: 9.00 Lac Base+ 2 Lac Retention Bonus+ 10K USD RSU‚Äôs- DevTest/ DevOps Role

Being responsive to our customers and delivering industry-leading mission-critical solutions require precise engineering and a philosophy of continuous improvement, both areas in which Zscaler engineers excel.

‚óè      Design and implement extremely high-volume, fault-tolerant, scalable backend systems that process and

12/04/23, 14:15 - Debjit Btech-F: JS Form ( form validation)

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
    <head>
        <title>JavaScript Form Demo</title>
        <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/style.css" />
    </head>
    <body>
        <div class="container">
            <form action="signup.html" method="post" id="signup">
                <h1>Sign Up</h1>
                <div class="field">
                    <label for="name">Name:</label>
                    <input type="text" id="name" name="name" placeholder="Enter your fullname" />
                    <small></small>
                </div>
                <div class="field">
                    <label for="email">Email:</label>
                    <input type="text" id="email" name="email" placeholder="Enter your email address" />
                    <small></small>
                </div>
                <div class="field">
                    <button type="submit" class="full">Subscribe</button>
                </div>
            </form>
        </div>
        <script>
            // show a message with a type of the input
    function showMessage(input, message, type) {
    // get the small element and set the message
    const msg = input.parentNode.querySelector("small");
    msg.innerText = message;
    // update the class for the input
    input.className = type ? "success": "error";
    return type;
    }

    function showError(input, message) {
    return showMessage(input, message, false);
    }

    function showSuccess(input) {
    return showMessage(input, "", true);
    }

    function hasValue(input, message) {
    if (input.value.trim() === "") {
        return showError(input, message);
    }
    return showSuccess(input);
    }

    function validateEmail(input, requiredMsg, invalidMsg) {
    // check if the value is not empty
    if (!hasValue(input, requiredMsg)) {
        return false;
    }
    // validate email format
    const emailRegex = (".+"))@((\[[0-9]{1,3}\.[0-9]{1,3}\.[0-9]{1,3}\.[0-9]{1,3}\])

    const email = input.value.trim();
    if (!emailRegex.test(email)) {
        return showError(input, invalidMsg);
    }
    return true;
    }

    const form = document.querySelector("#signup");

    const NAME_REQUIRED = "Please enter your name";
    const EMAIL_REQUIRED = "Please enter your email";
    const EMAIL_INVALID = "Please enter a correct email address format";

    form.addEventListener("submit", function (event) {
    // stop form submission
    event.preventDefault();

    // validate the form
    let nameValid = hasValue(form.elements["name"], NAME_REQUIRED);
    let emailValid = validateEmail(form.elements["email"], EMAIL_REQUIRED, EMAIL_INVALID);
    // if valid, submit the form.
    if (nameValid && emailValid) {
        alert("Demo only. No form was posted.");
    }
    });


        </script>
    </body>
</html>
12/04/23, 14:15 - Debjit Btech-F: Radio button

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>JavaScript Radio Button</title>
</head>
<body>
    <p>Select your size:</p>
    <div>
        <input type="radio" name="size" value="XS" id="xs">
        <label for="xs">XS</label>
    </div>
    <div>
        <input type="radio" name="size" value="S" id="s">
        <label for="s">S</label>
    </div>
    <div>
        <input type="radio" name="size" value="M" id="m">
        <label for="m">M</label>
    </div>
    <div>
        <input type="radio" name="size" value="L" id="l">
        <label for="l">L</label>
    </div>
    <div>
        <input type="radio" name="size" value="XL" id="xl">
        <label for="xl">XL</label>
    </div>
    <div>
        <input type="radio" name="size" value="XXL" id="xxl">
        <label for="xxl">XXL</label>
    </div>
    <p>
        <button id="btn">Show Selected Value</button>
    </p>

    <p id="output"></p>

    <script>
        const btn = document.querySelector('#btn');        
        const radioButtons = document.querySelectorAll('input[name="size"]');
        btn.addEventListener("click", () => {
            let selectedSize;
            for (const radioButton of radioButtons) {
                if (radioButton.checked) {
                    selectedSize = radioButton.value;
                    break;
                }
            }
            // show the output:
            output.innerText = selectedSize ? `You selected ${selectedSize}` : `You haven't selected any size`;
        });
    </script>
</body>
</html>

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>JavaScript input Event Demo</title>
</head>
<body>
    <label for="message">Message</label>
    <input placeholder="Enter some text" id="message" name="message">
    <p id="result"></p>
    <script>
        const message = document.querySelector('#message');
        const result = document.querySelector('#result');
        message.addEventListener('input', function () {
            result.textContent = this.value;
        });
    </script>
</body>

    let i1 = prompt("Enter first index:")
    let i2 = prompt("Enter second index:")
    i1 = parseInt(i1)
    i2 = parseInt(i2)
    const str = prompt("Enter String:")

    let temp = str.toLowerCase()
    let answer = document.getElementById('ans');
    if (temp[i1] == 'a' || temp[i1] == 'e' || temp[i1] == 'i' || temp[i1] == 'o' || temp[i1] == 'u')
        answer.innerText += str[i1]
    if (temp[i2] == 'a' || temp[i2] == 'e' || temp[i2] == 'i' || temp[i2] == 'o' || temp[i2] == 'u')
        answer.innerText += " " + str[i2]
</script>

30/01/24, 20:52 - Debjit Btech-F: Corporate Leadership (TCS - 803) is no longer a SWAYAM course. Hence, no registration/exam fees or SWAYAM certificate is required.
The course will now be operated on campus, as is typically done, following a course structure and standard textbook. Subsequently, the midsem and endsem examinations shall also be conducted on campus along with other subjects. Students who had to change electives due to it being a SWAYAM course can now keep the subject without any issues.
Kindly forward the update to your respective batchmates.

Thank you
